To improve the data model for `report_entity` based on the context provided and typical reporting use cases, we can enhance its structure to include additional metrics and fields that align with the expectations set by the `raw_data_entity.json`. Here’s a suggested schema for `report_entity`:

### Suggested Schema for `report_entity`

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Report Entity",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "report_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier for the report."
    },
    "generated_at": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "Timestamp when the report was generated."
    },
    "report_title": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Title of the report."
    },
    "summary": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "total_entries": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Total number of entries processed."
        },
        "successful_ingests": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Number of successful data ingests."
        },
        "failed_ingests": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Number of failed data ingests."
        },
        "percentage_success": {
          "type": "number",
          "format": "float",
          "description": "Percentage of successful ingests."
        },
        "total_active_brps": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Total number of active BRPs."
        },
        "total_inactive_brps": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Total number of inactive BRPs."
        }
      },
      "required": ["total_entries", "successful_ingests", "failed_ingests", "percentage_success"]
    },
    "details": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "active_brp_codes": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "description": "List of BRP codes that are active."
        },
        "inactive_brp_codes": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "description": "List of BRP codes that are inactive."
        },
        "report_generation_time_ms": {
          "type": "integer",
          "description": "Time taken to generate the report in milliseconds."
        },
        "comments": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "Additional comments or notes regarding the report."
        }
      },
      "required": ["active_brp_codes", "inactive_brp_codes", "report_generation_time_ms"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["report_id", "generated_at", "report_title", "summary", "details"]
}
```

### Enhancements Made:

- **Unique Identifier**: Added `report_id` to provide a unique identity for each report.
- **Detailed Summary**: The summary now has properties for `total_active_brps` and `total_inactive_brps` to gain insights into BRP statuses.
- **Detailed Information**: The `details` section includes both active and inactive BRP codes, enhancing tracking and reporting accuracy.
- **Comments Field**: A `comments` field allows for additional context or remarks regarding the report.

This improved structure is designed to be comprehensive, capturing the essential elements of a report entity while allowing for further data integrity and tracking. If you have specific requirements or further suggestions, please let me know!